d in the hints, which could be a gap if those are valid properties.\n\nNow looking at writeタグ, the hints list name, value, withHtmlFormat, and valueFormat, but I'm noticing the knowledge file includes \"HTMLエスケープ\" while the source documentation doesn't actually list htmlEscape as an attribute for writeタグ—unlike messageタグ which does have it. This might be an inaccuracy in the hints.\n\nActually, rereading the source more carefully, it says \"HTMLフォーマットはHTMLエスケープをする場合のみ有効となる,\" which means HTMLエスケープ is mentioned as a concept affecting withHtmlFormat's behavior rather than as a separate attribute. So the hint seems acceptable after all.\n\nBut I'm noticing a bigger issue with s4 (codeSelectタグ)—the hints are missing standard HTML attributes like size, multiple, disabled, tabindex, onfocus, onblur, onchange, and autofocus, all of which are listed in the source table as properties.\n\nLooking across the other sections, I'm seeing similar gaps. The validation guidelines specify that property names from tables should be included in hints, so these omissions are worth flagging as minor issues. Let me go through each section and note which standard attributes are missing from the hints. The S3 warning about 18 characters is actually correct since the source has no attributes. For the hints across sections 4-6, the missing entries are just standard HTML attributes like disabled and tabindex, which are minor issues. Looking at codeSelectタグ more carefully, the listFormat options in the source match what's documented—br, div, span, ul, ol, and sp for space-separated values are all accounted for correctly.\n\nNow I'm checking sections 5 and 6 for missing hints. Both codeRadioButtonsタグ and codeCheckboxesタグ are missing errorCss, disabled, onchange, and autofocus from their hint lists, even though these attributes appear in the source tables. Section 7's hints need checking too. I'm noticing that errorCss is inconsistently included across the hints sections—it appears in s1 and s2 but is missing from s4 through s7, even though it's a valid attribute in those components. The pattern suggests these hints need to be updated to include errorCss along with other missing attributes like disabled and onchange.\n\nNow I'm checking the V2 fabrication more carefully by comparing what the knowledge file claims against the actual source documentation. In s11, there's a discrepancy in how withHtmlFormat is described—the knowledge file has the full definition but the source appears to cut off mid-description, so I need to verify which version is accurate. Looking at the source documentation for the write tag, I can see the complete attribute table with name, value, withHtmlFormat, and valueFormat columns. The withHtmlFormat default is correctly shown as `true` in the knowledge file, and it controls whether HTML formatting (line breaks and space conversion) is applied when HTML escaping is enabled.\n\nComparing against the source, I notice some hints are missing from sections s4 through s7—specifically errorCss, disabled, and onchange attributes that should be documented. The HTMLエスケープ hint for s11 is actually valid since it's mentioned in the withHtmlFormat description, so that's acceptable. The main gap is those missing attribute hints from the earlier sections. Looking more carefully at the remaining sections, s1 preserves the ValidationResultMessage documentation link and all attributes with correct defaults, s9 includes the nonce generation context and sourceFormat attribute, and s12 correctly captures the deprecation notice. For s3, the noCacheタグ source genuinely has no attributes listed, so the brief 18-character representation is actually complete and accurate. The core findings remain: errorCss is the legitimate missing hint across s4-s7, and everything else checks out.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22554,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5